@startuml DarQuran_Live_Streaming_Clear

!define LIGHTBLUE #E1F5FE
!define LIGHTGREEN #E8F5E8
!define LIGHTYELLOW #FFF9C4
!define LIGHTPINK #FCE4EC
!define LIGHTGRAY #F5F5F5

title 🎥 DarQuran Live Streaming - Flux Simplifié

skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam rectangle {
    BackgroundColor LIGHTGRAY
    BorderColor #666666
    FontSize 12
}

' === ACTEURS ===
actor Enseignant as teacher #lightgreen
actor Élève as student #lightblue

' === ZONES FONCTIONNELLES ===
package "Frontend" LIGHTBLUE {
    [Angular App] as frontend
    [OBS Studio] as obs
}

package "Infrastructure Streaming" LIGHTYELLOW {
    [NGINX RTMP\nPort 1935] as nginx_rtmp
    [NGINX HTTP\nPort 8081] as nginx_http
    [Stockage HLS\n/tmp/hls/] as hls_storage
}

package "Backend API" LIGHTGREEN {
    [Spring Boot\nPort 8080] as api
    [UserNotificationService] as notification
    [LiveSessionService] as live_service
}

package "Persistance" LIGHTPINK {
    [PostgreSQL\nPort 5433] as db
    [Redis Cache\nPort 6379] as cache
    [MinIO S3\nPort 9000] as storage
}

' === FLUX PRINCIPAL ===

' 1. Création session
teacher -> frontend : 1. Créer session live
frontend -> api : POST /api/live/sessions
api -> db : Sauvegarder session\n(SCHEDULED)
api -> frontend : URLs générées\n(RTMP + HLS)

' 2. Configuration streaming
teacher -> obs : 2. Configuration OBS\nrtmp://server:1935/live/{key}
obs -> nginx_rtmp : 3. Flux RTMP\n(H.264 + AAC)
nginx_rtmp -> hls_storage : 4. Conversion HLS\n(.m3u8 + .ts)

' 3. Démarrage live
teacher -> frontend : 5. Démarrer live
frontend -> api : POST /sessions/{id}/start
api -> live_service : startStream()
live_service -> db : Update: LIVE + timestamp
live_service -> notification : dispatchLiveStarted()
notification -> teacher : 6. Notifications envoyées

' 4. Visualisation
student -> frontend : 7. Accéder au live
frontend -> api : GET /sessions (filtré)
api -> frontend : Sessions autorisées
frontend -> nginx_http : 8. Lecture HLS\n/hls/{key}.m3u8
nginx_http -> hls_storage : Récupération segments
hls_storage -> nginx_http : Flux .ts + playlist
nginx_http -> frontend : 9. Diffusion vidéo

' 5. Chat interaction
student -> frontend : 10. Poster commentaire
frontend -> api : POST /sessions/{id}/comments
api -> db : Persistance commentaire
frontend -> api : 11. Polling commentaires
api -> db : Récupération messages
db -> api : Liste comments
api -> frontend : Updates chat

' 6. Fin de session
teacher -> obs : 12. Arrêt streaming
obs -> nginx_rtmp : Fermeture RTMP
teacher -> frontend : Terminer session
frontend -> api : POST /sessions/{id}/end
api -> live_service : endStream()
live_service -> db : Update: ENDED
nginx_rtmp -> storage : 13. Upload MP4\n(si enregistrement)

' === NOTES EXPLICATIVES ===
note top of nginx_rtmp
  **NGINX RTMP**
  • Reçoit flux OBS
  • Convertit en HLS
  • Segments 1 seconde
end note

note bottom of api
  **Sécurité & Permissions**
  • JWT Authentication
  • Rôles: ADMIN/ENSEIGNANT/ÉLÈVE
  • Sections: HOMME/FEMME
  • Access: INTERNAL/EXTERNAL
end note

note right of db
  **Types de Sessions**
  SCHEDULED → LIVE → ENDED

  **Access Types**
  • EXTERNAL: Public
  • INTERNAL: Section only
end note

legend bottom
  |= Étape |= Description |= Technologie |
  | 1-2 | Configuration | Angular + OBS |
  | 3-4 | Streaming | RTMP → HLS |
  | 5-6 | Activation | Spring Boot API |
  | 7-9 | Diffusion | HLS Player |
  | 10-11 | Chat | REST API |
  | 12-13 | Clôture | Recording |
end legend

@enduml